sentences: Paul Okoye (born 18 November 1981), who is better known as Rudeboy, is a Nigerian singer, songwriter and record producer.
He rose to fame in the 2000s as a member of the P-Square duo with his identical twin brother Peter Okoye.
After the disbandment of P-Square in 2017, both band members sought separate musical careers.
Rudeboy released his debut solo tracks titled 'Fire Fire' and 'Nkenji Keke' in 2017.
His song "Reason With Me" generated the highest views on YouTube in Africa in 2019.
He is the founder of Fire Department Inc, a record label he established in 2019.
On 22 March 2014 Okoye married Anita Isama, whom he met in 2004 during his studies at the University of Abuja.

In 2013, their son Andre was born in Atlanta, Georgia, United States.
In August 2021, his wife filed for divorce due to irreconcilable differences with him.
